9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 613, L.D. 1529, “An Act to Enhance the
10 Protection of High-value Natural Resources Statewide”
11 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
12 following:
13 'Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §685-C, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2021, c. 676, Pt. A, §§23
14 and 24, is further amended to read:
15 1. Comprehensive land use plan. The commission shall prepare an official
16 comprehensive land use plan, referred to in this subsection as "the plan," for the
17 unorganized and deorganized areas of the State.
18 The commission must use the plan as a guide in developing specific land use standards and
19 delineating district boundaries and guiding development and generally fulfilling the
20 purposes of this chapter.
21 The plan may consist of maps, data and statements of present and prospective resource uses
22 that generally delineate the proper use of resources, and recommendations for its
23 implementation.
24 The commission shall hold public hearings to collect information to be used in establishing
25 the plan. The public hearings must be conducted according to commission rules adopted in
26 accordance with procedures for the establishment of rules pursuant to Title 5, chapter 375,
27 subchapter 2.
28 The commission may, on its own motion or petition of any state agency or regional
29 planning commission, hold such other hearings as the commission considers necessary
30 from time to time for the purpose of obtaining information helpful in the determination of
31 its policies, the carrying out of its duties or the formulation of its land use standards or
32 rules.
33 A. The commission may not finalize a plan or a portion of a plan without:
34 (1) Submitting a draft copy of the tentative plan to each regional planning
35 commission and other appropriate planning or state resource agencies, which shall
