316 forward their comments and recommendations, if any, to the commission within
327 30 days;
3 (2) Submitting a draft copy of the tentative plan to the Director of the Bureau of
4 Resource Information and Land Use Planning within the Department of
5 Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, Bureau of Resource Information and Land
6 Use Planning, as described in Title 7‑A, section 206, subsection 4, or its the
7 director's successor, which who shall forward its the director's comments and
8 recommendations, if any, to the commission within 30 days; and
9 (3) Considering all comments and recommendations submitted under paragraphs
10 A and B‑1; and subparagraphs (1) and (2).
11 (4) Submitting the tentative plan to the joint standing committee of the Legislature
12 having jurisdiction over conservation matters and the committee reviewing the
13 plan at a public meeting. The commission shall brief the committee on any
14 anticipated changes to land use districts and subdistricts based on revisions in the
15 comprehensive land use plan and a projected timetable for rulemaking to adopt
16 these changes.
17 B-1. After the commission has finalized provisionally adopted a plan or a portion of a
18 plan, but prior to final adoption, the commission shall provide a copy to the
19 Commissioner of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry, who shall submit the
20 finalized provisionally adopted plan or a portion of the plan to the Governor for
21 comments. The commissioner shall submit the finalized provisionally adopted plan or
22 a portion of the plan, including the Governor's comments, to the Legislature within 30
23 days after the convening of for approval during the next regular legislative session for
24 approval. The Legislature shall, by act or resolve, approve, disapprove or require
25 changes to the provisionally adopted plan or any portion of the plan prior to
26 adjournment. If the provisionally adopted plan or a portion of the plan is approved or
27 the Legislature fails to act on the provisionally adopted plan or a portion of the plan
28 before adjournment, the provisionally adopted plan or a portion of the plan may be
29 finally adopted by the commission. If the provisionally adopted plan or a portion of
30 the plan is disapproved or revisions are required, the provisionally adopted plan or a
31 portion of the plan must be revised by the commission and resubmitted to the
32 Legislature for approval by act or resolve. The joint standing committee of the
33 Legislature having jurisdiction over conservation matters may submit legislation to
34 implement the provisions of this paragraph.
35 This subsection also applies to any material alteration in the plan.
36 Sec. 2. 12 MRSA §8879, sub-§1-B is enacted to read:
37 1-B. Report on conservation of late-successional forests and old-growth forests.
38 Beginning with the report due on January 1, 2031, the report must include information
39 regarding the status of late-successional forests and old-growth forests in the State and
40 actions that have been taken since the previous report under this section to enhance the
41 conservation of late-successional forests and old-growth forests on public and private land
42 statewide.
43 Sec. 3. Maine Land Use Planning Commission; comprehensive land use
44 plan. The Maine Land Use Planning Commission, referred to in this section as "the
Page 2 - 132LR1424(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 613, L.D. 1529
415 commission," shall, as part of the next update to the comprehensive land use plan under the
426 Maine Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 685-C, subsection 1, consider the effectiveness
437 of its lake management program and whether changing circumstances and new trends
448 warrant an update to the program, including an evaluation as to whether all lakes or a subset
459 of lakes should be reclassified, what methods should be used to revise lake classifications
560 if needed, the cost of the reclassifications, possible funding sources and the priority for
571 implementation. The evaluation must consider whether additional measures are required
582 to protect the character and natural resource values of the commission's current
593 Management Class 7 lakes that are undeveloped and have one or more natural resources
1504 classified as outstanding by the Department of Conservation, Land Use Regulation
1515 Commission's Maine Wildlands Lake Assessment published in 1987 in accordance with
1526 the commission's goal of maintaining an appropriate balance between conservation and
1537 development.
14 Sec. 4. Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry to develop
15 comprehensive report on statewide strategies to enhance conservation of late-
16 successional forests and old-growth forests. The Department of Agriculture,
17 Conservation and Forestry, referred to in this section as "the department," shall develop a
18 comprehensive report on statewide strategies to enhance the conservation of late-
19 successional forests and old-growth forests, including the management of transitioning
20 late-successional forests. In developing the strategies, the department shall incorporate
21 ecological values, carbon sequestration methods and economic considerations from a broad
22 range of perspectives to include forest landowners, forest industry representatives, logging
23 contractors, conservation interests and local economies. By November 4, 2026, the
24 department shall submit the report, including any recommendations, to the joint standing
25 committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over agriculture, conservation and forestry
26 matters, which may report out legislation related to the report to the 133rd Legislature in
27 2027. In completing the report required by this subsection, the department may solicit and
28 use resources from other state agencies and outside sources.
29 Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
30 allocations are made.
31 AGRICULTURE, CONSERVATION AND FORESTRY, DEPARTMENT OF
32 Forest Resource Management Z233
33 Initiative: Provides one-time funding for contractual services to assist with research, data
34 compilation, statistical analysis and report writing.
