COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 613, L.D. 1529
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment replaces the bill. The amendment provides that the Maine Land Use
33 Planning Commission may not finalize a comprehensive land use plan under the Maine
44 Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 685-C, subsection 1 or portion of a plan without:
55 submitting a draft copy of the plan to each regional planning commission and other
66 appropriate planning or state resource agencies; submitting a draft copy of the plan to the
77 Director of the Bureau of Resource Information and Land Use Planning within the
88 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry; and consider all comments and
99 recommendations submitted.
10 The amendment changes the date that the Director of the Bureau of Forestry within the
11 Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry is required to include information
12 regarding late-successional forests and old-growth forests in the director’s report on the
13 state of the State’s forests from January 1, 2026 in the bill to January 1, 2031.
14 The amendment directs the Maine Land Use Planning Commission, as part of the next
15 update to the comprehensive land use plan, to consider the effectiveness of its lake
16 management program and whether changing circumstances and new trends warrant an
17 update to the program.
18 The amendment also directs the Department of Agriculture, Conservation and Forestry
19 to develop a comprehensive report on statewide strategies to enhance the conservation of
20 late-successional forests and old-growth forests, including the management of transitioning
21 late-successional forests. The department is required to submit a report by November 4,
22 2026 to the joint standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over agriculture,
23 conservation and forestry matters, which may report out legislation related to the report to
24 the 133rd Legislature in 2027.
